For example, I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>knew</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that our last <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> raid would be punctuated with post-wipeout rez waiting, so I bound myself at the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Fiorana Vie</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> bank.  When the inevitable death occured, I withdraw a few plat from the bank, bought some <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malachite</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Cat's Eye Agates</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and otherwise naked except for summoned items, went fishing in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Lake Fillomen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  With only gems <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (I deliberately left my back up equipment in the bank just to prove a point)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I was able to solo blue <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Deepwater</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bloodgill Barracudas</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  After I was finally rezzed, my experience bar was ahead of where I was when I died.<br>
<br>
Whereas <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rythax</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was forced to stand there without his pants twiddling his thumbs for an hour.<br>
<br>
I admit I like goodies, but they do not make or break us the way it does melee classes.<br>
