<br>
In PoG, there are treants that cast a spell called silence.  Ever heard of it?  When a caster has it, you cannot cast spells.  Period.  <br>
<br>
When you take on a god, near 95% of your spells get resisted.  Which means besides pet (which you dont get to have on lots of raids anyways) you are near useless.  When does this ever happen with melee?  When do they suddenly become 100% ineffective?<br>
<br>
In order to make mobs harder, VI gave them more HP, harder hits/nukes, and near immunity to spells.  But look at what that does...   Melee can still hit, but casters can't cast.  How is this balanced?  Sure the melee takes a ton more damage from these creatures, but compare that to 100% resist on your nukes.  Now which do you think is less usefull?  <br>
<br>
I like VI's idea, they are on the right track.  But the implementation needs alot of work.  They are making it such that about 3 classes out of 12 are needed.  That just does not work in my book.<br>
<br>
WTF is up with hate mobs on 2nd floor???  Seriously, that blows chunks!  Hate = mage needed planer zone.  Our gear and epic pieces drop there right?  So why make pathing so bad that pets are not allowed, then make the new mobs have such high resist that I'm near useless there too??  hmmm, <br>
<br>
&quot;no pet, no nukes....  would you like a bandage?  Oh, nm, you have a cleric.  I think I'll go sit in the corner now...&quot;<br>
<br>
Have you ever looked at how truely useless the lvl 56 anti summoned nuke is??  NO advantages, no faster cast, no good mana ratio, and it only works on 1% of the mobs in the game???  Did they even THINK about that before they made it??  I don't think so.<br>
<br>
Please fix this verant, it needs work.  And so do your balancing skills. <p><center><img src="http://www.homestead.com/balandar/files/eandori.jpg" width=173
