The only thing that would make caster items actually improve the caster are:<br>
<br>
1) mana regen, adressed by FT, but it sucks.  FT1 = 1 mana a tick, in a minute it would get you 10 mana back, 10! ten mana means nothing at the level where you get these items.  FT2 = 2 mana per tick, same as breeze.  Same thing, means nothing.  The only FT2 item I know of are the boots from giving Tormax's head to Yelinak, I'm sure there are some for Giant people too, but thats all I know of.  However, FT3-10 are in the spell dat, and may one day appear in game (SoL most likely, if ever).<br>
<br>
2) effects, Velious sorta addressed this, though we started seeing them in Kunark, but rarely.  I know we had stuff from the old world with effects like our focus items, but I mean more than that.  Unfortunately, a free spell has to have its down side.  Huge cast time, or other limitations (like Donal's BP).  With the new &quot;no sitting while casting items&quot; fix, these aren't that useful in many cases.  Mage pants are, imo, they save a spell slot and you only lose 5% haste.  Necro robe is sweet.  But over all, they suck.<br>
<br>
3) focus items, Supposedly we'll get these in SoL.  Similar to pet focuses, when wearing these items, your spell are more effective.  For example, Nukes reduced in cast time, mana, more damage, less resists.  Heals heal more, cost less, cast faster (may actually cause problems for clerics timing heals on the main tanks to start with).  However, casters are so powerful without equipment that if these are really awesome it will totally unbalance the game.  Tough I'd imagine that the new uber mobs in SoL will counter the new armor, but it unbalances the rest of the world.  I expect these to be similar to FT (a let down), but am hoping for the best. <p>~~
